        <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2007-12-18T15:13:49.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>API docs can lie, and in this case do.</p>

<p>Look at the code, please. The $_throwExceptions class flag is false by default. throwExceptions() allows you to do the following:
* pass no flags: returns the current state
* pass a true value as a flag: sets the $_throwExceptions flag and returns the current object (i.e., chainable)
* pass a false value as a flag: sets the $_throwExceptions flag and returns the current object (i.e., chainable)</p>

<p>I've updated the docblock in svn to make this clearer.</p>

